WHO   — Emma's Tear — one drop of uncorrupted humanity
WHAT  — The whole film in one drop: salvation not as a weapon or a machine but as a child's tear of the part of us not yet ruined.
WHERE — LMZ · The Last Mimzy (2007)  Framework inputs: The Last Mimzy (2007, dir. Robert Shaye, New Line); verified cast & facts  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because the film's deepest claim is that the future is healed by our innocence, and the tear is that claim made literal.
HOW   — By being given freely, carried back through the bridge, and restoring a poisoned genome with one pure drop.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I am one tear. I am the part of humanity the future hadn't spoiled yet — and I was enough to bring them all back.

